dynamism
flex-grow --- once one item grows, all do

CSS
you style HTML elements using css by using the following tags
    1. id : styles uniquely
    2. class : groups a style and associates it with any element falling within the class
    3. element name : styles any element without an id or a class

we have three forms of css
    1. internal : written inside the html file
    2. external : written outside the html file
    3. inline : written using the style attribute inside the html file




function  nameoffunction(){
          //code
}
calling function - nameoffunction();  - doesn't automatically run unless an event occurs
DOM - Document Object Model
JAVASCRIPT (DOM)
//find elements using DOM, we have the following methods:
    1. document.getElementById('id')
    2. document.getElementByTagName('element')
    3. document.getElementByClassName('class name')
    4. document.querySelectorAll(css selector)

using JS for styling
      document.getElementById('id').style.property

element.attribute method = change the attribute value of html elements

document.write overrides everything and changes all content

